 the origin of the inferred correlation between giant planet\nfrequency and host star mass in the exoplanet population, and provides some\nbasic support for the core accretion model for planet formation. Moreover, we\ncaution that selection bias must be considered in comparative studies of disk\nevolution, and illustrate that fact with statistical comparisons of L_mm\nbetween Taurus and other clusters (abridged).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 22 May 2013 20:40:00 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 13 Jun 2013 13:53:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-16"}
