ian extensions $\\Delta_F$ and $\\Delta_B$, proving\nthat $\\Delta_F$ is stochastically complete at the singularity if and only if\n$\\alpha\\le -1$, while $\\Delta_B$ is always stochastically complete at the\nsingularity.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 22 May 2013 21:12:36 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 23 Jul 2013 08:29:48 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 29 Oct 2014 16:38:48 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Wed, 7 Oct 2015 12:53:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-06-21"}
